originalText.text:
One of the worst KTV places I have been to.
Cheapest liquor on earth for “flat rate” customers. I looked up the gin bottle they use for drinks - it’s a $9 retail price bottle (“Skol gin”). That should tell you everything.
The rooms are super old, dated and not very clean. The KTV control is an old huge controller with buttons… not intuitive controlling at all. The karaoke voice score didn’t work - it gave every time 00 score. And the light in the bar went out for 10min (?)
I have unfortunately nothing positive to report. Pick another KTV place in K Town - there are plenty

originalText.text: Deceptive business. They’ll try to offer a bottle package when you book, but when you got there it’s $100/hr per room + $100 min drink order *per hour*. Ridiculous. Go to literally any other karaoke place in ktown which will not mandate these minimums. They’ll also slap on an outrageous 25% tip mandatory. Avoid at all costs.

originalText.text: we came here after the new year’s eve countdown around 2:15am and we were told by a guy working in the bar that we can no longer get a room for karaoke because they are closing in 30minutes and after that I relayed the information to my group and we understand. However, when we decided to just get some drinks the guy that works in the bar keeps on ignoring us and the girl that was also working with him was sooo busy entertaining other customers in the bar and we guess it was their friends because they were feeling so close.

originalText.text: Don’t go to this place. Twice the have scammed my friends and I. They force you to pay a 25% tip on all bills and don’t tell you at the start. They won’t let you lower it. They don’t care if you don’t know, and they often keep you in the dark so you tip twice. Terrible business. It’s fun because it’s karaoke, but you can get that anywhere that doesn’t treat you like a milkable source of cash like this place. I really tried to enjoy this place, but they always manage to ruin the experience by the end.

originalText.text: I had an amazing experience at Anytime Karaoke! The highlight for me was their fantastic selection of Bollywood music, which made the night unforgettable. The staff was incredibly accommodating and allowed us to extend our time, ensuring we had a blast throughout the evening. Not only was the karaoke top-notch, but the food and drinks they offered were also delicious and varied. The combination of great music, extended time, and scrumptious refreshments made for a perfect night out. I can't wait to return for more memorable moments! 5 stars all the way!
